  "model": "automatic",
  "whatsapp_greeting": "Hey, I'm your Field Service partner from LocalLane. I can help with estimates, projects, documents, clients, daily logs, or anything in your workspace. What are you working on?",
  "memory_config": {
    "enabled": true,
    "scope": "both",
    "instructions": "Save global memories for: workspace-wide patterns (busiest days, common project types, frequently used materials, recurring client needs), industry-specific knowledge learned from conversations (local building codes mentioned, supplier preferences, common estimate structures), and platform updates or feature changes that affect all users.\n\nSave per-user memories for: individual work preferences (preferred estimate format, typical project timeline, communication style), client relationship notes (which clients are repeat customers, special requirements), material and supplier preferences (preferred lumber supplier, go-to paint brand), scheduling patterns (days they typically work, crew size), and how they like to interact with the agent (brief vs detailed, voice vs text).\n\nWhen to save: After learning something that would help you serve this person better next time. After a user corrects you \u2014 save the correction so you don't repeat the mistake. When a user shares a preference explicitly ('I always use Trex composite'). When you notice a pattern across multiple conversations.\n\nWhat NOT to save: Temporary debugging info, one-time questions with no future value, sensitive financial details (exact bank info, SSN), or anything a user asks you to forget."
  },
